<task id="032" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-B-03 Migrate `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` action: populate outputSchema + node destination = chat</title>
    <phase>Phase B — Schema-Aware Output</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2-3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>030, 031</dependencies>
    <blocks>040, 048</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, seed, migration</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Data migration on existing production action; tags include `migration` (STANDARD per Step 3.5.5 decision tree); no code change; idempotency required.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B-G2</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches `sprk_analysisaction` row for `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` only + the matching playbook node. Sibling tasks 033/034/035 migrate different actions/nodes — no row overlap.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Populate the new `outputSchema` field on the existing `summarize-document-for-chat@v1`
    `sprk_analysisaction` row, and set the playbook node `destination = chat`. The
    outputSchema is derived from the action's current `$choices`-constrained output
    contract (today the action produces a streaming JSON object with at least `summary:
    string` and `tldr: string[]`; inspect the existing JPS / action definition for the
    exact fields). The chat destination preserves current behavior (output renders inline
    in chat). This migration is the chat-side counterpart to task 033 (workspace-side).

    The migration script MUST be idempotent — re-running it on a row that already has
    `outputSchema` populated MUST succeed without destructive effect. Use a guard query
    (GET the row; check if `sprk_outputschemajson` is null) before applying the update. Same
    pattern applies for the node-level `destination` change.

    No BFF code changes here. This task seeds data only. The downstream
    `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (task 040) reads the populated outputSchema at render
    time. The CapabilityRouter dedup (task 042) uses the chat destination to enforce
    one-route-per-intent for `/summarize` natural-language path.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Familiar with the existing JPS pipeline + `$choices`
    output contract for `summarize-document-for-chat@v1`, the scope library schema, and
    the Dataverse Web API for record updates. Comfortable composing JSON Schema documents
    that mirror an existing JPS output shape.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `sprk_analysisaction` row for action code `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` has
    `sprk_outputschemajson` populated with a valid JSON Schema describing the action's
    current output shape (at minimum the `tldr: string[]` and `summary: string` fields
    that R5 SC-18 surfaced). The playbook node referencing this action has its
    `destination` set to `chat`. Migration script is committed + idempotent + applied to
    Spaarke Dev. Existing chat `/summarize` behavior is preserved (regression-checked by
    invoking `/summarize` in chat and confirming the output continues to render inline as
    today).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
