  <context>
    <background>
      `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` (action code `SUM-CHAT@v1`) is the chat-side
      summarization action exercised by R5 SC-18. R5 surfaced two rendering bugs the
      schema-aware widget (tasks 040, 041) will fix — `tldr: string[]` rendering as raw
      JSON tokens; `entities: { orgs, persons }` rendering as raw JSON literal. This
      migration declares the output shape as data so the widget can dispatch on field
      type at render time.

      The playbook node referencing this action also gets `destination = chat`, which is
      consumed by `DeliverOutput` (NFR-08 unmodified) to confirm the output is delivered
      to chat (the current behavior). When task 042 CapabilityRouter dedup lands, the
      chat destination on this node is what proves "/summarize natural-language path
      routes to ONE rendering — chat".
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>scripts/Migrate-SumChatActionOutputSchema.ps1 (NEW)</file>
      <file>infra/dataverse/outputschemas/sum-chat-v1.schema.json (NEW — versioned schema document referenced by migration script)</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/task-032-migration-evidence.md (NEW)</file>
    </relevant-files>
    <related-work>
      <item>Sibling tasks 033 (workspace), 034 (matter-prefill), 035 (project-prefill) migrate the other 3 actions in parallel (B-G2).</item>
      <item>Task 040 widget array-rendering depends on this migration being applied.</item>
      <item>Task 042 CapabilityRouter dedup relies on the chat destination set here.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL">
      Check context. Declare:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD
      📋 REASON: Data migration on production action; idempotency required; no code change;
                 tag `migration`
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS: 8 steps; Step 9.5 quality gates SKIPPED per STANDARD rigor
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read TASK-INDEX.md; confirm 032 status 🔲; deps (030, 031) complete. Verify
      `sprk_outputschemajson` column exists on `sprk_analysisaction` (deployed by task 030).
      Verify node config supports `destination` (task 031).
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read inputs + knowledge files. Inspect the JPS source for SUM-CHAT@v1 (search
      `infra/dataverse/` or `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Playbook/`
      seed data for the action definition). Identify the concrete output fields
      (at minimum `summary: string`, `tldr: string[]`; inspect for entities or other
      array/object-typed fields).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Author the JSON Schema Document">
      Create `infra/dataverse/outputschemas/sum-chat-v1.schema.json` — a draft-07 JSON
      Schema document describing the SUM-CHAT@v1 output. Validate it against the
      meta-schema. Diff against any matter/project pre-fill action outputSchema (tasks
      034, 035) for consistency in style.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Author Migration Script">
      Create `scripts/Migrate-SumChatActionOutputSchema.ps1`. Script:
      (a) connects to Spaarke Dev;
      (b) GETs action row by alternate key `sprk_actioncode = 'summarize-document-for-chat@v1'`
          (or equivalent — verify actual code in JPS source);
      (c) checks `sprk_outputschemajson` — if null, PATCHes with schema content; if matches,
          skip; if mismatches, FAIL with conflict;
      (d) GETs the playbook node referencing the action; PATCHes node config to set
          `destination = chat` (per task 031 storage surface);
      (e) logs all actions taken.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Apply to Spaarke Dev">
      Run the migration script. Capture output + the post-migration GET response showing
      `sprk_outputschemajson` populated + node `destination = chat`. Record in
      `notes/task-032-migration-evidence.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify Idempotency">
      Re-run script. Confirm: no error; no destructive effect.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Regression Smoke Test">
      Invoke chat `/summarize` against a test document. Confirm output continues to
      render in chat (existing behavior preserved). The widget is NOT yet schema-aware
      (that's task 040), so rendering looks identical to today — the schema is declared
      but not yet consumed by the renderer.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Confirm Acceptance + Complete">
      Walk through acceptance criteria. Update TASK-INDEX.md: 032 🔲 → ✅. Reset
      `current-task.md`. Report completion. Note BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB.
    </step>
  </steps>

